`,t.jsx(n.li,{children:"What was the intent?"}),`
`,t.jsx(n.li,{children:"What was the prior version?"}),`
`,t.jsx(n.li,{children:"What validation ran after the change?"}),`
`,t.jsx(n.li,{children:"Which output became canonical?"}),`
`]}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:'If the answer is "read the transcript and infer it," the system is not production-ready.'}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"The clean pattern is simple: the model sees context, but the application owns state. Every meaningful change updates durable state with enough metadata to reconstruct what happened."}),`
`,t.jsx(n.h2,{id:"tools-are-backend-apis-not-magic",children:t.jsx(n.a,{href:"#tools-are-backend-apis-not-magic",children:"Tools are backend APIs, not magic"})}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"Tool calling is where agents stop being chat and start being software."}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"That is also where risk enters."}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"A tool is not just a function the model can call. It is a capability exposed to an uncertain decision-maker. The model may choose the wrong tool, choose the right tool with wrong arguments, retry at the wrong time, or interpret a partial failure as success."}),`
