`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:'Retrieval-augmented generation is often described as "give the model relevant context."'}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"That is true, but incomplete."}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"Production retrieval needs to define what happens when context is missing, stale, conflicting, unauthorized, or too broad."}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"The common failure mode is quiet overconfidence. Retrieval returns something adjacent to the question, the model reasons over it, and the answer sounds plausible. The user does not see the miss."}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"For high-stakes systems, retrieval should fail visibly."}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"Good retrieval systems answer:"}),`
`,t.jsxs(n.ul,{children:[`
