`})}),`
`,t.jsxs(n.p,{children:["Each Map iteration receives a minimal payload: ",t.jsx(n.code,{children:"testRunId"}),", ",t.jsx(n.code,{children:"testSuiteId"}),", ",t.jsx(n.code,{children:"marketplace"}),", and retry count. Detailed test results live in DynamoDB, not in the workflow payload, so the state machine stays well under Step Functions payload limits."]}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"The Map state tolerates individual iteration failures. Failed marketplace executions return standardized failure results to the collector. They do not terminate the whole workflow. This was the key product behavior: a UK timeout should not erase US and DE results."}),`
`,t.jsx(n.h3,{id:"test-data-locking",children:t.jsx(n.a,{href:"#test-data-locking",children:"Test-data locking"})}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"Test data is a shared, limited pool. A configuration represents a complete set of concrete bindings for one test suite and marketplace. Two concurrent executions cannot safely use the same data."}),`
`,t.jsx(n.p,{children:"The orchestrator locks test data with DynamoDB conditional writes:"}),`
`,t.jsxs(n.ul,{children:[`
`,t.jsxs(n.li,{children:["acquire only if the configuration is ",t.jsx(n.code,{children:"ACTIVE"}),";"]}),`
`,t.jsxs(n.li,{children:["mark it ",t.jsx(n.code,{children:"LOCKED"})," with ",t.jsx(n.code,{children:"lockedBy = testRunId"}),";"]}),`
